stylometry: Transportation problem is problem that is shipping something from point A to point B. These are usually origins and destinations. Transshipment problem is similar to transportation problem but it also contains nodes. Nodes are neither origins or destinations but are locations where shipments can be shipped to to reduce costs. Both transportation and transhipment problems can have arcs which are pathways or routes to ship and have flow which is the number of items being shipped throughout the arcs. Example of a transshipment problem is lets say a oil company has two oil wells and needs to ship oil to L.A and NewYork. The cost to ship directly to these two locations are extremely high. The oil company also has two warehouses where they can ship oil to and reship it to LA and NewYork and inccur less shipping costs. What is the optimal shipment path that the oil company can choose to minimize the cost to ship oil.
